The paper deals with the problem of sequential compressed sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The use of Gaussian or Gaussian mixture models and linear projections suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of covariance estimation is also related to statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the use of compressive measurements and signal estimation suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
